Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>
Dynamically set architecture-specific paths

Revert "Handling EC2 Health Scheduled Events"

This commit reverts the following Scheduled Events related commits:
* edeb81e2caddf6b67ec66e58828c1663bd54b85b
* 613c43d9aaf943c67e6caa1ce3c69f8d2bc1e0bd
* 8876b8f8dd1178cd74b72eea887fd94924612868
* fb9d07b7ff1b1e6fb6708f4218dffc7e85ef6cd2
* 13eb8e405b449f1b99c4dc8e48fc831154bb2912

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Scheduled Events: Bug Fixes

* Fixed bug in nodewatcher slurm plugin `lock_host`. Added unit test for this function.
* Addressed comments from previous review

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Scheduled Events: Address Minor Comments

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Scheduled Events: Better error handling

* Failure when locking/unlocking nodes: preserving existing behavior by catching the error locally in locking function. Calling functions have logic to deal with locking failures.
* Failure when retrieving node state/node info: Raise the error, and handle the error in the calling functions such as `is_node_down` and `is_node_locked`
* Failure in `sqswatcher` actions: added extra try statement to prevent sqswatcher from crashing.
* Added unit tests

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Scheduled Events: Address Review Comments

* Refactored implementation code according to review comments

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Handling EC2 Health Scheduled Events

* Modified sqswatcher to retrieve and process messages from health queue. Lock instance if there is an EC2 health scheduled event, so that instance can be replaced by nodewatcher ASAP
* Modified nodewatcher to consider nodes that are locked and have no job as down nodes
* Modified unit tests to adapt to above modifications
* This feature can be turned off by specifying `disable_health_check = True` in `/etc/sqswatcher.cfg` and restarting sqswatcher

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Bump version to v2.7.0

Signed-off-by: ddeidda <ddeidda@amazon.com>

commit.message:
Bump version to 2.6.1

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

Changelog v2.6.1

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

SGE: do not consider u(nknown) nodes as busy in jobwatcher

* Modify SGE_BUSY_STATES to not consider a node with u(nknown) state as busy in order to avoid overscaling issue when sge process is temporarily unresponsive when hitting bottleneck on network, etc in a large scale setting
* nodewatcher should already take care of replacing a node if it is consistently in u state
* Modified unit test to adapt to above changes

Signed-off-by: Rex <shuningc@amazon.com>

Only log count of pending jobs in nodewatcher log

* Add an optional parameter to the get_pending_jobs_info function for
each of the scheduler commands modules that enables the suppression of a
log message containing every pending job.
* Add a log message for the count of pending jobs that is always logged.
* Suppress the log message containing all pending jobs when calling the
function from nodewatcher.

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

Only log slurm node list if it's been modified

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

Standardize logging when getting pending jobs

Generate log messages describing the pending jobs found in the common
scheduler commands modules instead of duplicating the same calls in the
scheduler-specific plugins for each of the daemons.

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

Don't log insufficient node resources message

Avoid generating a log message that states an existing node does not
have sufficient resources (e.g., slots) to run a job. If a message were
logged for this case, it would lead to log pollution in the case of a
cluster with many compute nodes and many pending jobs that could not be
placed on any of those nodes.

Signed-off-by: Tim Lane <tilne@amazon.com>

sqswatcher: delete from queue messages that are discarded due to hostname collision

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

Reducing retries for failed REMOVE events from 2 to 1

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

slurm_commands: reduce log noise from job_runnable_on_given_node

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

jobwatcher: retrieve busy nodes before computing required ones

If jobs are scheduled to nodes between the moment the jobwatcher
computes the number of requried nodes (based on the pending jobs) and
when the list of busy nodes is fetched then the cluster over-scales.
Moving get_busy_nodes before get_required_nodes in order to prevent
this from happening.

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

Removed unused imports

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>

sqswatcher - slurm: increasing parallelism when restarting slurmd on compute nodes

Signed-off-by: Francesco De Martino <fdm@amazon.com>
